page.title: 03MY DAY (CHILD) LIVERTON
page.content: I am{Catherine Grogory.}I am eleven years old. My mum wakes me at 7.10am and I have breakfast(which is usually cereal)at 8.15am. My mum drives me to school at 8.30am and I arrive at 8.45am. My school is{Blackpool C of E {Primary:}a school of 140 pupils just outside the village of{Liverton.}At school we have{House Captains,Games {Captains}and{Prefects.}I am a prefect. We normally start the day with S.M.P. a maths scheme. Then at 10.30am we have a break. After break we do some english work. Our lunch break is 12.15pm to 1.30pm. After lunch we have assembly and then art,games or other activities. At 3.30pm we leave school and I go to my parents shop,where I have some tea and practise my piano. At 5.30pm we leave the shop and go home. Later on I go to bed.
